# NPTEL Hub - Frontend

## Environment Setup

Create a `.env.local` file:

```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api
NEXT_PUBLIC_SOCKET_URL=http://localhost:5000
```

## Installation

```bash
npm install
```

## Running Locally

Development mode:
```bash
npm run dev
```

Build for production:
```bash
npm run build
npm start
```

## Project Structure

```
src/
├── app/              # Next.js App Router pages
├── components/       # React components
├── lib/             # Utilities (API, Socket.io)
├── store/           # Zustand state management
└── app/globals.css  # Tailwind CSS
```

## Key Components

### Sidebar (`components/Sidebar.jsx`)
- Hierarchical navigation: Subject > Course > Year > Week
- Smooth animations and folding
- Responsive sidebar toggling

### WeekDetail (`components/WeekDetail.jsx`)
- Three-tab system: PYQs, Chat, Community Vault
- Video lecture links
- Past year questions display

### ChatRoom (`components/ChatRoom.jsx`)
- Real-time Socket.io integration
- Message threads with reply-to
- Reactions and emoji support
- Typing indicators

### ResourceVault (`components/ResourceVault.jsx`)
- Grid-based resource display
- Upvote/downvote voting system
- Resource filtering by type
- External link handling

### Authentication Pages
- `/login` - User login with JWT
- `/register` - New user registration
- Token stored in localStorage and sent via Authorization header

## State Management (Zustand)

Global store at `src/store/useStore.js`:
- `user` - Current authenticated user
- `token` - JWT token
- `messages` - Chat messages in active room
- `resources` - Week resources
- `selectedSubject/Course/Year/Week` - Navigation state

## API Integration

All API calls use `src/lib/api.js`:
- `authAPI` - Registration, login, password reset
- `courseAPI` - Subjects and courses
- `yearInstanceAPI` - Year instances and weeks
- `resourceAPI` - Resources with CRUD operations

## Socket.io Events

Client-side event handling in `src/lib/socket.js`:
- Join/leave rooms
- Message CRUD operations
- Reactions and threading
- Typing indicators

## Security

- JWT tokens stored in localStorage
- Authorization header for protected routes
- Input sanitization on backend
- HTTPS in production
- CORS configured for backend

## Styling

- Tailwind CSS for utility-first styling
- Responsive design (mobile-first)
- Dark mode ready (can be extended)
- Lucide React for icons

## Deployment

### Vercel (Recommended)
```bash
npm install -g vercel
vercel
```

### Docker
See `Dockerfile` in root directory

### Environment for Production
```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.nptel-hub.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_SOCKET_URL=https://api.nptel-hub.com
```

